`when(mockMvc.throwException(any(Exception.class)))` 문장을 삭제하고, `/test-exceptions/general` 경로의 컨트롤러 메소드 (`throwGeneralException()`)가 예외를 직접 발생시키도록 수정했습니다.

The problem lies in the fact that you are trying to test a custom exception handler for general exceptions, but your controller method `throwGeneralException()` is declared to throw an `Exception` instead of one of your custom exceptions.

To fix this issue, you should modify the `throwGeneralException()` method to throw one of your custom exceptions. For example:

```java
@GetMapping("/general")
public void throwGeneralException() throws BusinessException {
    throw new BusinessException(ResponseCode.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);
}
```

Alternatively, if you want to test a general exception without throwing a specific exception, you can modify the `throwGeneralException()` method to catch all exceptions and throw a custom exception:

```java
@GetMapping("/general")
public void throwGeneralException() throws Exception {
    try {
        // Code that might throw an exception
    } catch (Exception e) {
        throw new BusinessException(ResponseCode.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);
    }
}
```

However, keep in mind that this approach is not recommended as it can mask the original cause of the exception. It's better to test a specific scenario where your custom exception handler is triggered.

Also, make sure that your custom exception handler is properly configured and registered in your application. If you are using Spring Boot, you should have a configuration class with `@ExceptionHandler` annotations pointing to your custom exception handlers.

```java
@RestControllerAdvice
public class CustomExceptionHandler {

    @ExceptionHandler(BusinessException.class)
    public ResponseEntity<ErrorResponse> handleBusinessException(BusinessException e) {
        // Handle business exception
    }

    @ExceptionHandler(Exception.class)
    public ResponseEntity<ErrorResponse> handleGeneralException(Exception e) {
        // Handle general exception
    }
}
